Diagnosis.
Forewings (
Fig. 19
) brownish with black veins, costal margin yellowish. Aedeagus (
Figs 26, 27
) with atrial processes wide; shaft wider at mid-length from where two pairs of processes arise: one shorter and curved, directed anterad, and one longer and straight directed dorsad.

Coloration.
Head and thorax (
Fig. 16
) yellowish brown. Face (
Fig. 17
) without maculae. Crown (
Fig. 16
) with two rounded black spot behind ocelli near posterior margin. Pronotum (
Fig. 16
) in dorsal view, with posterior margin darkened; in lateral view (
Fig. 18
), proepimeron without maculae. Forewings (
Fig. 19
) brownish with black veins, costal margin yellowish, apex dark brown. Legs yellowish.

Male terminalia.
Sternite VIII (
Fig. 20
) 1.4 times wider than long; posterior margin broadly rounded with middle portion strongly produced. Pygofer (
Fig. 21
) 1.8 times longer than maximum height; dorsal margin with short process at base; apex blunt; posterior margin (
Fig. 22
), in ventral view, without protrusion. Subgenital plate (
Fig. 23
) 3.3 times longer than wide; maximum width near base and gradually tapered toward apex; apex rounded. Connective (
Fig. 24
) T-shaped, with rami shorter than stalk; stalk long and wide. Style (
Fig. 24
), in dorsal view, with outer lobe truncated; in lateral view (
Fig. 25
), ventral protrusion two times longer than its maximum width, apex rounded and serrated; blade approximately straight and slightly wider toward apex, apex emarginated with two apical teeth. Aedeagus (
Figs 26, 27
) with atrial processes wide, shell-like, narrow at base, with rounded notch on anterior margin near apex; shaft wider at mid-length from where two pairs of processes arise: one shorter and curved, directed anterad, and one longer and straight, directed dorsad; apex of shaft slender, with anterior portion membranous and without processes.

Female terminalia.
Sternite VII (
Fig. 28
) 1.6 times wider than long; posterolateral corners rounded; posterior margin slightly sinuous. Pygofer (
Fig. 29
) 1.4 times longer than maximum height, apical margin weakly rounded. First valvifer (
Fig. 30
) 1.9 times higher than long. First and second valves (
Figs 30, 31
) as in the generic description.
